<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Flock2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Flock,</orth> vb., to gather and repair in crowds: <cit><quote>they f. together in consent,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.1.78" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 1, 78</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>many young gentlemen f. to him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.123" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 1, 123</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.8.5" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 8, 5</bibl>. <cit><quote>f. to follow him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.209" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 209</bibl></cit>. <emph>f. to their aid,</emph> R3<bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.4.507" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 507</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>